summary: SummaryNow with 24HR Shine Control, Laura Mercier's Translucent Loose Setting Powder is a cult-favorite, award-winning silky powder with a touch of sheer coverage to set and maintain makeup for up to 16 hours of wear with a soft-focus finish and zero flashback.
details: DetailsBenefits#1 setting powder*Instant blurring effect16-hour soft matte finishNo photo flashbackDoes not clog poresDermatologist-testedSuitable for all skin typesNon-comedogenic24hrs of shine control*Based on #1 US Rank by NPD Group Inc. in Prestige Retail, YE 2021.FeaturesBeloved for Blurring: 92% of consumers say the powder instantly blurs imperfections.****16-hour soft matte finish: Sets makeup for 16-hours of transfer resistant wear, with 95% of consumers saying it controls oil all day.****Reduces shine: 86% of consumers say the powder reduces shine throughout the day.***Feels breathable: 95% of consumers say the ultra finely-milled powders feel lightweight on skin and allow skin to breathe.****No texture: 89% of consumers say the powder doesn't settle into imperfections and never looks cakey.****No photo flashback: Take the no photo flashback test and say good-bye to flashback!Truly translucent: 84% of consumers say the powder is translucent upon application for a naturally flawless look.****Smoothing effect: 94% of consumers say the powder gives a smooth look to skin!****Foolproof: Artist-inspired ''press & roll'' technique ensures the perfect application every time, with 91% of consumers saying it applies effortlessly.*******Based on Consumer Perception Study of 63 subjects with Translucent Loose Setting Powder and Flawless Lumière****Based on Consumer Perception Study of 63 subjects with Translucent Loose Setting Powder aloneKey IngredientsVitamin C + E Powders: Powerful antioxidants known to support a more even toned complexion overtimeBotanical Blurring Powder: silky, finely-milled plant derived powder blurs the looks of pores and absorbs excess oilSkin Conditioning Powder: natural amino acid powder that melts into skin for an undetectable finishUltra, Finely-Milled Texture: becomes one with skin, without emphasizing texture, imperfections, or dry patchesItem 2562494How To UsePrep Laura Mercier's Velour Puff (sold separately) by massaging Translucent Loose Setting Powder into the puff, folding both halves together. Tap the powdered side on the back of your hand to remove excess. Fold the puff in half and gently press and roll the puff onto skin to set your makeup. Around the eyes, use Laura Mercier's Secret Brightening Powder for Under Eyes (sold separately). Focus on the areas where makeup breaks down the most. Apply after any creamy formulas, including cream blush.Tip: Renowned Makeup Artist Laura Mercier uses it to set foundation and prolong its wear. She applies it after foundation and concealer, and before applying powder-based color. As an added benefit, it eases the application of powder blush or bronzer.IngredientsTranslucent Medium Deep: Talc, Magnesium Myristate, Nylon-12, Caprylic/ Capric Triglyceride, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Zea Mays (Corn) Starch, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Methylparaben, Lauroyl Lysine, Propylparaben, Polymethyl Methacrylate, Methicone, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Butylparaben, Tocopherol. May Contain: CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 (Iron Oxides), CI 77007 (Ultramarines).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Prep Laura Mercier's Velour Puff (sold separately) by massaging Translucent Loose Setting Powder into the puff, folding both halves together. Tap the powdered side on the back of your hand to remove excess. Fold the puff in half and gently press and roll the puff onto skin to set your makeup. Around the eyes, use Laura Mercier's Secret Brightening Powder for Under Eyes (sold separately). Focus on the areas where makeup breaks down the most. Apply after any creamy formulas, including cream blush.Tip: Renowned Makeup Artist Laura Mercier uses it to set foundation and prolong its wear. She applies it after foundation and concealer, and before applying powder-based color. As an added benefit, it eases the application of powder blush or bronzer.

reviews.headline: I would buy this powder again and again!
reviews.comments: This powder is a magic in a bottle! Really, it makes my under eyes crease-proof and smooth. Love how natural is my skin after using this. Also it fixes my makeup perfectly throughout the day and gives smooth, matte but not too much finish. I love it so much! It is the best I can say!

reviews.headline: One of my favorites
reviews.comments: Without a doubt, it's been one of my favorite powders for years. It's 100% ideal for client makeup. I use the translucent one on most of my clients, and we achieve an instant flawless effect that lasts for hours at whatever event they're at.

reviews.headline: Perfect Powder
reviews.comments: I finally bit the bullet and bought this expensive powder! It really is a great setting powder that is translucent with a matte finish. Keeps the oil and shine away all day, which is a feat here in hot, humid Georgia! The price is up there but the powder does like everyone says it does and it will last a very long time. So to me, it's worth it. I recommend! At least try the mini version first before splurging!

reviews.headline: The best translucent powder
reviews.comments: I love how it leaves my skin as if it were a filter, its blur effect is spectacular, it helps me show off my makeup at 100%. I also like that it brightens my face but leaves a matte finish! And when I take a photo, my face doesn't look white—it's a success!

reviews.headline: My holy grail!
reviews.comments: Ive been using this setting powder for the past couple years and its my favorite! It sets your makeup beautifully and doesnt leave you looking cakey. Your makeup will last. I highly recommend this setting powder to EVERYONE!

reviews.headline: Great
reviews.comments: Love it

reviews.headline: Best setting powder!
reviews.comments: This has been the best setting powder for under my eyes. It gives a soft and blurred look. Last all day!

reviews.headline: Love it, but container is not usable
reviews.comments: While I love this powder, getting it out of the container is extremely difficult. My husband has to take a drill to get a big enough hole in the top so I can scoop all the powder out and put in another container. I use a brush to place on my face and i cannot do that the way this container is made. Despite loving this product, I won't be buying it again just because of the container.

reviews.headline: Sets Makeup Amazing
reviews.comments: This is a must have for my makeup routine and I use it daily. It sets my makeup really well and helps it last all day. I love that it controls shine and and helps with my oily skin. It is really easy to apply and it feels lightweight on my skin too.

reviews.headline: Must have
reviews.comments: The Laura Mercier Translucent Setting Powder is iconic for a reason.  This is a must-have in my makeup routine.  It does a brilliant job blurring pores and gives my makeup a flawless finish.  I appreciate that it does not crease or settle into my fine lines.  Incredible product!

reviews.headline: I LOVE THIS POWDER
reviews.comments: this poweder is literally the best powder ive ever used. everyone needs to try this powder. mattifies my makeup ALL DAY and is super effective.

reviews.headline: Immediate Compliments on my skin
reviews.comments: I purchased this because my normal makeup look was looking more shiny in this God forsaken heat and needed a finish. I noticed how great this pressed powder was right after I applied it. THEN I went to a Love Island watch party and when I met up with my long-time friends, the first comments made were about how great my skin looked. So yeah. This stuff is worth it.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Okay so I have always wanted to try this but kept putting it off. I didn't think I needed to spend the $ when there are so many alternatives. I was using the coty one for a while however it put a pink cast all over my face when I have yellow/neutral undertones. So it made my foundation look like the wrong undertone due to the powder itself. I also realized when my oils did come through it looked extremely cakey and separated. So finally I caved and tried this & I'm in love. I'll never use anything else. It's got a yellow neutral undertone but doesn't effect the color of your foundation, the tone of it is just enough to not give that white cast and not too strong so it doesn't effect your shade altogether. It's also super finely milled, more than any other powder I've tried, you also don't need as much as the cheaper brands (I think). Lastly, when my oils start to break through in my T zone with this powder it doesn't give that cakey look it more so give a natural glow back to your foundation without being oily or overly matte. Hopefully that makes sense! 
Long story short if you're debating it just do it!
faceoff_positive.headline: Worth it.

faceoff_negative.comments: I was excited to try this product, as I've been in need of a good setting powder to hold my makeup in place and combat a bit of shine. I did my due diligence researching this product, reading online reviews, perusing blog posts, and watching top-rated beauty vloggers reviews. After doing this homework, I decided to make the purchase because it seemed like a sure-thing. While this product does perform as it claims--sets makeup, matte finish, soft-focus effect--it does, however, introduce a problem that cancels out its benefits. What is the problem? Oxidization! After about twenty to twenty-five minutes of wear, it turned my makeup red-orange. This may not be a problem for those who have deep skin with red undertones, but I don't. I have dark/deep skin with yellow. I was in public when it oxidized, and very uncomfortable with my very visible pumpkin skin. My lipstick and clothing colors ceased to compliment my complexion, as well. I find this to be an issue with reputable makeup companies who are trying in earnest to reach a more diverse clientele. The darker shades turn red or orange. That, or they wrongly assume deeper skin doesn't have yellow undertones. I have faith LM will either re-formulate or introduce another shade that can be worn for those of us who have dark or deep skin with yellow undertones. In the meantime, I've found wearing a little of this without any foundation makes my natural skin look heavenly--the oxidization isn't noticeable, it stands up against heat and sweat, and my dynamic complexion comes through. So, it turns out I purchased a surprise product I didn't know I wanted.
faceoff_negative.headline: Feels lovely, absorbs shine, oxidizes red/orange...
